title: Build WordPress Sites That Attract Free Traffic
headline: Learn how to use SEO and WordPress to attract free traffic from Google in this free online course.
description: In this free online course you will learn how to build a WordPress website that brings in visitors using SEO (search engine optimisation). Start the course and master the latest techniques for free, high quality traffic by getting the best out of your hosting providors, keywords and google rankings. Learn from an instructor who has been building and optimising WordPress websites since 2004.

courseDescription:
This free online course begins with a brief introduction to what you will be doing in the course, including how to evaluate niches, evergreen niches, primary niches and sub-niches which will help you decide what you want to focus on. Next, you will learn how to build out the WordPress site framework with the end goal of a fully SEO optimised website.

The course then moves on to studying factors such as click through rate and the length of an article, that determine which web pages rank on page one of Google, Yahoo and Bing. It also covers how Google uses RankBrain to evaluate the user experience of your content helping you to start creating content that ranks on page one.

Finally, having made some developments to the website and having ticked all the SEO boxes, the course moves on to the last stage, where you start to get some shares, likes and overall social media visibility, collectively referred to as social signals. You will also learn how to get backlinks, and how to find out which backlinks our competitors have. Start this course today and learn valualbe skills on how to use SEO and WordPress to attract free traffic from Google.

Start Course Now

modules.name: Module
modules.description: This module explains the advantages of SEO (Search Engine Optimisation) for generating free traffic. Learn about what's possible with free traffic, and find out what you will be learning and doing in this course.

modules.name: Module
modules.details: What Will Your Website be About?
modules.description: In this module you will learn about evergreen niches, primary niches, secondary niches and sub-niches
topics: Deciding on a Niche or a Subject for Your Website

modules.name: Module
modules.description: In this module you will build your website using best practices and create a good foundation for adding search engine optimised content.
topics: Important 'To Do' Tasks in Your Hosting Account

modules.name: Module
modules.details: Ranking Your Content - What You Need to Know
modules.description: This module explains Google's ranking factors and what determines which websites and content rank on Page 1 of the search results. Learn about 'RankBrain', 'user experience'm and understand what Google wants. Fortunately, SEO is a level playing field and the old ranking 'tricks' no longer work. This is good news for anyone creating a new website with the intention of attracting free traffic from the search engines.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: In this module you will learn how to create the kind of content that Google and the other search engines 'like'.
topics: Keyword Research for Website Posts and Articles
Writing Compelling Posts/Articles and Meta Tags

modules.name: Module
modules.description: This module shows you how to use best SEO practices to optimise your website content

modules.name: Module
modules.details: How to Structure Your Website for Best Results
modules.description: Website structure plays an important part in attracting free traffic from the search engines and this module covers everything you need to know on this subject
topics: Navigation, URL's, Loading Speeds, and More

modules.name: Module
modules.description: In this module you will learn what Social Signals are and how to create and build up Social Signals for your WordPress website. You will also learn how to get 'backlinks' (incoming links from other relevant websites).

modules.name: Module
modules.details: Using Video as Part of Your SEO Strategy
modules.description: Video can be a powerful medium for free Google traffic. In this module you will learn about ranking videos on page 1 of the Google search results, using YouTube (which is owned by Google)
topics: Ranking Videos in the Search Results
